Sentencas: We report a new nickel-iron alloy nanoparticle-decorated LaSrFe0.75Ni0.25O4 K2NiF4-type oxide with Ruddlesden-Popper structure (RP-LSFN), which performed as a high-performance sulfur-resistant anode prepared by using an infiltration method for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with LaSrFeNiO6-delta double perovskite (DP-LSFN) as the precursor.
Titulo: Nickel-Iron Alloy Nanoparticle-Decorated K2NiF4-Type Oxide as an Efficient and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A reduction converts the DP-LSFN phase into mixed phases containing the RP-LSFN and FeNi3 nanoparticles.
Titulo: Nickel-Iron Alloy Nanoparticle-Decorated K2NiF4-Type Oxide as an Efficient and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The morphology, thermal expansion behavior, sulfur tolerance, and electrochemical activity for hydrogen oxidation of this FeNi3 nanoparticle-decorated, RP-LSFN-infiltrated anode are investigated.
Titulo: Nickel-Iron Alloy Nanoparticle-Decorated K2NiF4-Type Oxide as an Efficient and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: An electrolyte-supported SOFC with this infiltrated anode generates a high power output of 541 mWcm(-2) at 800 degrees C operated with 1000 ppm H2S-H-2 as the fuel, which compares favorably to that with pure H-2 fuel.
Titulo: Nickel-Iron Alloy Nanoparticle-Decorated K2NiF4-Type Oxide as an Efficient and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A single cell with this anode demonstrates favorable stability at 800 degrees C during 90, 40, and 20 h operation with H-2 containing 100, 200, and 1000 ppm H2S, respectively.
Titulo: Nickel-Iron Alloy Nanoparticle-Decorated K2NiF4-Type Oxide as an Efficient and Sulfur-Tolerant Anode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
